wbqc-violation-message-type:
Message for a violation of the “Type” or “Value type” constraint, when an entity (either the subject or the object of a statement) should have a certain type but doesn't. Parameters:
* $1 is {{msg-mw|Wbqc-violation-message-type-entity-type}} or {{msg-mw|Wbqc-violation-message-type-entity-valueType}};
* $2 is {{msg-mw|wbqc-violation-message-type-relation-instance}} or {{msg-mw|wbqc-violation-message-type-relation-subclass}};
* $3 is the entity that doesn't have the required type;
* $4 is the number of classes;
* $5 is an HTML list of all classes;
* and $6, $7 etc. are the individual classes.
